  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the feasibility of acquisition of coronary blood
      flow velocity signals over the whole length of the LAD with transthoracic pulsed Doppler, and
      to evaluate the diagnostic power of the transthoracic Doppler analysis package for detecting
      and estimating the degree of coronary artery stenosis. Finally we hope to optimize the
      currently available analysis package on the basis of the comparison of the Doppler with the
      angiographic stenosis results and evaluation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
